1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,799
A task lands in Codex. HQ treats it like a project, not a chat reply.

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:15,800
HQ assigns roles, ownership, and review responsibility before work starts.

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:23,800
The agents challenge the plan. Weak shortcuts are rejected early.

4
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:31,800
Memory opens first, so old failures are not repeated.

5
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:39,799
Work moves through visible states: planned, building, blocked, validating, and reviewed.

6
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:47,799
The build produces files, demos, docs, and validation checks.

7
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:55,799
Risky actions stop at deferred gates until a human approves.

8
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:03,799
Telegram becomes the ops console: approve, reject, pause, retry, status, and logs.

9
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:11,799
Validation happens before confidence. Evidence beats vibes.

10
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:19,799
Telemetry records what worked, what failed, and what the next session should remember.

11
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:27,799
Agent HQ OS connects memory, agents, queues, gates, Telegram control, validation, and telemetry.
